                                      ACCESS SPECIFIERS/ MODIFIERS
                                  ====================================

-> These are used to specify  accessibility for our classes ,variables and methods.
-> In java, we have below 4  access specifiers.

    1.Public
    2.Private 
    3.Protected
    4.Default

Public: It is used to specify  global access for classes, variables, methods and Constructors.

      ->we can take class as public 
      ->constructor as public 
      ->variables and methods also we can take as public  

NOTE: if we use " public " for the class name then class name & file name should be same . We should have only one public class in the java file.

Private: It is used to specify local access.Private variable,private methods,private constructors can't be accessed outside of the class.
      
      ->we can't use private for class(it is not allowed )
      ->we can take variables , methods, constructors as private 


Protected: Protected members can be accessed in same package and sub classes.

Default: Default members can be accessed in same package.
      NOTE: only public and default specifires are allowed for classes. Private and protected are not allowed.




















